claim.claim-text:
1. A photovoltaic cell, comprising:
a substrate having a top surface and formed from a first electrically conductive material, that is etched on said top surface to create an array of grooves, such that said grooves have walls and a floor;
an array of micrometer or nanometer sized rods, wires, or tubes formed from said first electrically conductive material deposited on said array of grooves vertically with respect to the floor of said grooves, with gaps in between each said rods, wires or tubes of said array of rods, wires, or tubes;
a layer of second electrically conductive material deposited conformally on said rods, wires or tubes and said substrate, covering exposed surface of said rods, wires or tubes and said substrate, such that said layer forms charge separating junctions at interfaces with said rods, wires or tubes, and said substrate;
a first electrode electrically connected to said layer; and
a second electrode electrically connected to said substrate;
wherein the walls of said grooves are vertical or inclined at a specific angle with respect to the top surface of said substrate.

9. A photovoltaic cell, comprising:
a substrate that is etched to create an array of grooves, wherein each said groove has walls and a bottom surface which is substantially flat;
an array of micrometer or nanometer sized rods, wires, or tubes of first electrically conductive material deposited in said array of grooves vertically with respect to the bottom surface of said grooves, with gaps in between each rods, wires, or tubes of said array of rods, wires or tubes;
at least one layer of second electrically conductive material disposed on said substrate, such that said rods, wires or tubes are embedded in said at least one layer of second electrically conductive material, and charge separating junctions are formed at interfaces with said rods, wires or tubes and said substrate;
a first electrode electrically connected to said at least one layer of second electrically conductive material; and
at second electrode electrically connected to said substrate;
wherein the walls of each of said grooves are vertical or inclined at a specific angle with respect to the bottom surface of each of said grooves.

17. A photovoltaic cell, comprising:
a supporting substrate;
a first layer formed from first electrically conductive material and grown on said supporting substrate,
wherein said first layer is etched to create an array of grooves, and
wherein each of said grooves has walls and a bottom surface which is substantially flat;

an array of micrometer or nanometer sized rods, wires, or tubes formed from first electrically conductive material and grown in said array of grooves vertically with respect to the bottom surface of said grooves, with gaps in between said rods, wires or tubes;
at least one second layer formed from second electrically conductive material and grown on said first layer, surrounding said rods, wires or tubes, such that charge separating junctions are formed at interfaces with said rods, wires or tubes and said first layer;
a first electrode electrically connected to said at least one second layer; and
a second electrode electrically connected to said first;
wherein the walls of each of said grooves are vertical or inclined at a specific angle with respect to the bottom surface of each of said grooves.
